.TH "git alias.rewindbase(1) User manual" "" "May, 2020" "" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
git rewindbase
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
git rewindbase source - move a branch to the common ancestor with its
upstream
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
git rewindbase is a helper alias to force move a branch to the common
ancestor with its upstream.
.IP "1." 3
Ensures that the proper number of arguments have been provided
.IP "2." 3
Ensures that the provided argument is associated with a branch
.IP "3." 3
Ensures that the provided branch is associated with an upstream branch
.IP "4." 3
Stores the upstream branch name associated with HEAD in a variable
.IP "5." 3
Finds and stores the merge base between the provided branch and its
upstream
.IP "6." 3
Calls\ branch -f to force the provided branch pointer back to its common
base with its upstream
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
git rewindbase master
.SH SEE ALSO
.SH DETAILS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
rewindbase = \[dq]!f() { : git man rewindbase; \[rs]
    [ $# -ne 1 ] && echo \[aq]Usage: rewindbase source\[aq] && return 1; \[rs]
    if ! git show-ref $1; then echo $1 \[aq]not a named ref\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    if ! git rev-parse --abbrev-ref $1\[at]{u}; then echo \[aq]no upstream branch\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    UPSTREAM=$(git rev-parse --abbrev-ref $1\[at]{u}); \[rs]
    BASE=$(git merge-base $1 $UPSTREAM); \[rs]
    git branch -f $1 $BASE; \[rs]
}; f\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
